1 packet Creamy Pesto Dressing
1 Red Onion
1 sachet Garlic & Herb Seasoning
4 herbed pork sausage
1 packet Baby Leaves
1 packet Grated Parmesan Cheese
1 Carrot
1 Parsnip
1 packet Peeled Pumpkin Pieces
1 drizzle balsamic vinegar
1 drizzle olive oil

• Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced. Cut parsnip and carrot into bite-sized chunks. Cut onion (see ingredients) into wedges.
• Place veggies on a lined oven tray. Sprinkle over half the garlic & herb seasoning, drizzle with olive oil, season with salt and toss to coat.
• Spread out evenly, then place pork sausages on one side of the tray.
• Roast until tender, 20-25 minutes.
Little cooks: Help toss the veggies.

• Meanwhile, place herbed pork sausages on a second lined oven tray, drizzle with olive oil and turn to coat.
• Bake until cooked through, 12-16 minutes.

• When veggies and sausages are done, combine all veggies on one tray with baby spinach leaves and a drizzle of balsamic vinegar. Season to taste.

• Divide roast veggie toss between plates.
• Top with pork sausages. Dollop over dill & parsley mayonnaise to serve. Sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese. Enjoy!
Little cooks: Add the finishing touch by drizzling over the mayo!